reviewText: I love this show, they take some  autos in very bad shape and turn them into some very good looking and running works of art. The main thing is they are keeping them on the road where they should be instead getting crushed in junk yards.

reviewText: A fun and cute show when it's free, but I would not pay for this show. Half way through watching the first series Prime started charging for this series, exactly at the time Prime announced that they were raising rates. They said it was a "coincidence!" It's just not worth paying to see this.
summary: Was free on Prime, but now they want you to pay!

reviewText: Better than Pimp My Ride because the modifications to the cars are artful, tasteful, and functional.  They actually rebuild engines and do other things to recondition the entire car.  No bowling ball cleaners in the trunk or anything lame like that.
summary: Pretty cool to watch, especially for car enthusiasts.
